The Machine Translation Toolpack for LoonyBin

See http://www.cs.cmu.edu/~jhclark/loonybin for more documentation.


QUICKSTART

First, obtain and unpack LoonyBin on your desktop/laptop.

Download and unpack the LoonyBin tool pack in the same directory on your desktop/laptop.

Download, unpack, *and run install-dependencies.py* on all machines that will execute
some part of your workflows.

Double-click the LoonyBin.jar file to start the GUI. Load an example workflow
such as tool-packs/machine-translation/workflows/joshua.work. And generate
a bash script.